Throughout my time at Kyiv School of Economics, I had the privilege of meeting incredible people whose guidance and knowledge have had a profound impact on my education and personal growth.

First of all, I want to express my deep gratitude to my supervisor, Ihor Pysmennyi. I am deeply grateful to Ihor for supporting our app idea from the very beginning, believing in us and helping us throughout the entire process with both generating ideas and ensuring their proper implementation. I am very glad that our journey began with the API development course. Although I was a little nervous about the rapid transition to the practical side during the first lesson, I quickly got into the process. The course was incredibly interesting and useful, as I was able to immediately apply this knowledge in real life.

I am also deeply grateful to our Academic Director and lecturer Artem Korotenko. Thanks to Artem, my programming journey began. As a complete beginner during my first year, entering the world of coding was made much smoother thanks to his high level of expertise. I was able to learn complex concepts and stay motivated to continue developing in this field. This is why I consider Artem the foundational mentor of my professional knowledge.

I would like to express special gratitude to lecturers Vadym Yaremenko and Denys Zavhorodnii. They have had a significant impact on my desire to improve and achieve my goals. Their professional approach to teaching and their ability to present complex information in an easily understandable way are extremely important to me. Thanks to them, I could clearly see my progress in class, realized I was capable of more and always knew exactly who to turn to for reliable advice whenever needed.

I am sincerely grateful to KSE for the opportunity to learn and grow, which was remarkably challenging amid the full-scale war. I am very thankful for the lecturers I had the chance to work with, for the people who studied alongside me and for the opportunity to gain valuable life and professional experience.

Finally, I want to thank my family, who believed in me through it all, always listened to my academic stories both joyful and difficult and sincerely supported and shared every success with me.

*Collaborative Work Acknowledgement:* I would like to express my deepest gratitude to my project partner, co-developer and dear friend Kateryna Shashkina. Thanks to her knowledge, creativity, endless stream of new ideas, hard work and belief in our abilities, we were able to fully realize our initial vision and even achieve more. I am incredibly happy and proud that Kateryna was my partner on this journey. Without her, it would have been difficult to achieve this result.